      "title": "Presence Australia",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The first day of the first Test of the two - match series against Sri Lanka, which started today in Galle, saw Australia's presence during the lunch break.",
        "Sri Lanka, the first team to bat in the tournament, lost 2 wickets in their first innings and scored 68 runs. Currently, skipper Timothy Karunaratne is unbeaten on 25 and Anjalo Mathews on 15. Captains Burr Cummins and Mitchell Starc took one wicket each."
      ],
